laboratory_examinations.findings: 1-mm horizontal ST-segment depression in V6 and borderline 1-mm ST-segment elevation in V4R.
Demonstrated normal coronary arteries; small apical aneurysm containing a radiolucent filling defect was visualized.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Filling defect in the apical aneurysm was not seen during subsequent evaluation 5 months later.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Revealed a small apical aneurysm characteristic of a remnant from a sump used to vent the left ventricle during surgery; 2 discrete areas of transmural delayed gadolinium enhancement corresponding to infarct territories; left ventricular (LV) systolic function was mildly depressed with an ejection fraction of 44%.
Demonstrated a left hemothorax and pneumothorax; seventh rib fractures were noted, with no extravasation of contrast observed.
